        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 5:06PM CDT by NWS Huntsville AL</headline>
        <description>At 506 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Phil Campbell, or 11 miles north of Haleyville, moving
south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Russellville, Moulton, Phil Campbell, Mt Hope, Speake, Isbell,
Bankhead National Forest, Spruce Pine, Wren, and Landersville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
